The Diesel Exhaust Fluid Heater Relay Override Test cannot continue because Diesel Exhaust Fluid Concentration or Diesel Exhaust Fluid Temperature sensor faults are active. Please troubleshoot any active fault codes prior to restarting the test.

The Diesel Exhaust Fluid Heater Relay Override Test cannot continue because the test has exceeded the maximum number of allowable overrides. Please cycle the Keyswitch and restart the test. If necessary, allow the Diesel Exhaust Fluid Tank Temperature to cool before restarting the test.

The Diesel Exhaust Fluid Heater Relay Override Test cannot continue because the Diesel Exhaust Fluid Heater is disabled.
Diesel Exhaust Fluid Doser Pump Override Test running.
The Diesel Exhaust Fluid Doser Pump Override Test cannot continue because the engine is not running. Please restart the test with the engine running.

The Diesel Exhaust Fluid Doser Pump Override Test cannot continue because faults for Diesel Exhaust Fluid Quality, Diesel Exhaust Fluid Temperature, or Diesel Exhaust Fluid Level are active. Please troubleshoot any active fault codes prior to restarting the test. In addition, make sure the Diesel Exhaust Fluid Doser has proper air pressure and Diesel Exhaust Fluid supply.
The Diesel Exhaust Fluid Doser Pump Override Test has completed.

The Diesel Exhaust Fluid Doser Pump Override Test cannot continue because the Diesel Exhaust Fluid in the Diesel Exhaust Fluid Tank is too cold to dose. Please allow enough time for the Diesel Exhaust Fluid temperature to increase.

The Diesel Exhaust Fluid Doser Pump Override Test cannot continue because the Diesel Exhaust Fluid in the Doser Tank is too cold to dose. Please allow enough time for the Diesel Exhaust Fluid temperature to increase.
The Diesel Exhaust Fluid Doser Pump Override Test cannot continue because the Diesel Exhaust Fluid Level is too low. Please add Diesel Exhaust Fluid prior to restarting the test.

The Diesel Exhaust Fluid Doser Pump failed to prime. Please troubleshoot any active fault codes prior to restarting the test. In addition, make sure the Diesel Exhaust Fluid Doser has proper air pressure and Diesel Exhaust Fluid supply.
Diesel Exhaust Fluid Doser Air Solenoid Click Test running.

The Diesel Exhaust Fluid Doser Air Solenoid Click Test could not be started because communication between the ECM and Air Solenoid could not be established. Please troubleshoot the fault codes prior to restarting the test.

The Diesel Exhaust Fluid Doser Air Solenoid Click Test could not be started because the ECM and Air Solenoid Pump have incompatible software. Please troubleshoot the fault codes prior to restarting the test.
